<br>
As for the pathing, which is indeed whacky at times, the trick is not getting so far ahead that they warp on you. Don't cast at full range, cut it closer if you can. Even though you can cast without line of sight, don't.<br>
<br>
I enter from the center, or north-facing, entrance to the caves. I can manage to kill the first four spawns before I start getting respawns that are in the kite path (there is one off to the left that is not within aggro range when kiting any of the other 3).<br>
<br>
I have RS3, epic, FT2, familiar up and KEI. I use approx. 65% to 70% of my mana on one kill. Here's magelo for comparison: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=445067">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=445067</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I always kill the one on the left first. By the time I have medded/harvested to full after killing the third one, the first one has respawned. Have not bothered to time it yet, but I would guesstimate 12 min respawn.<br>
<br>
Use Voltaic Draught or Draught of Jiva.<br>
<br>
Obviously this is not too efficient a way to get the shimmerings to spawn, but it works for those times when I cannot get a partner or two. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.paegen.com/images/vec_sig.jpg" alt="Invectus Stormborn" border="0">
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=invectus>Invectus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/27/03 2:51:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=niellya>Niellya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/27/03 6:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for tips on soloing Geos in WL for 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> I solo'd them for several of my gems.  Level 56 with non-uber equipment.  Used the following technique.<br>
<br>
On horseback.<br>
Root<br>
Markar's Discord<br>
Voltaic Draught<br>
Markar's Clash<br>
Voltaic Draught<br>
Root<br>
Repeat<br>
<br>
If there are two of them close to each other you can (most of the time) Flux Staff single pull one away (on foot and then root and bring the horse up).   <br>
<br>
This way you don't run into pathing issues as they don't move much between roots / stuns.<br>
<br>
