<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.circleofradiance.com">Circle of Radiance</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alindawyl>Alindawyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/28/03 2:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for tips on soloing Geos in WL for 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> I quadded them when I was going after shawl 8.  At the time I had FT2, epic, and Greater Familiar with a mana pool around 3500.  Pillar of Lightning since they have no MR to speak of.  Pulled with clicky until I went KOS and then pulled with snare.<br>
<br>
The main thing is getting them out of the cave.  If you let them hit a wall and get stuck, one of two things will happen.  Usually they warp on you, like normal, but occasionally they warp under the ground and get stuck there (but still following you and hitting you because of that dumb Z axis thing).  To prevent them from falling through the world, make SURE they don't get stuck running into a wall.  Takes a little practice, but eventually you'll get the hang of it.<br>
<br>
With C2 or better I could do two quads before repops.  I shared the main entrance with a druid for a while and there was plenty for both of us to pull and kill without getting too deep in or trying to draw from Phenocryst's room.<br>
<br>
Shamans slow you down because you have to kill them single.  But the shamans can drop good loot (blue diamonds or decent cash gems) so it's not too bad.  While getting the gems for my shawl I think I got 4 blue diamonds and a good bit of plat from cash gems.<br>
<br>
But get ready for lots of duplicates.  Invariably you'll get a string of like five of one gem type in a row.  Doing geos with a fellow shawl seeker is more efficient, as you can trade off gem loots.  The druid had his diamonds and I had my sapphires so we sent tells if a type we didn't need dropped.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ktadema>ktadema</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/1/03 4:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for tips on soloing Geos in WL for 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the responses, they helped a lot.  What helped me even more were the numerous patches, server resets, et al that occurred during the week.  It seemed like everytime I gated and looked around the geo tunnels in WL, I'd find 3-4 Shimmering Geos up everytime.  Thanks to that, I have 4 of every gem type now.  <br>
<br>
The tactic I ended up using as a 60th level wizard was snaring one at a time and nuking them down.  In all honesty, I was terrified at first.  ALL of the geos conn'd dark blue to me.  Even though they were amiable (from the Pheno quest), I feared pulling a Shimmering in the middle of 8-9 other geos, thinking they might all gang bang me in a tunnel without being able to outrun them with my RS3.  Turns out that they don't help each other.  However, Geo shamans will heal their wounded Shimmering geo buddies, which isn't a big surprise.  <br>
I also came out pretty lucky on gem drops.  I never had a long run of one type of gem. <br>
<br>
Only thing I'm missing now is one more hound fur and 3 large bricks of velium.  Thanks for the help all. <p>Givins, 60th level Erudite Wizard, Rodcet Nife  </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tzarphkaboom>Tzarph Kaboom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/03 8:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for tips on soloing Geos in WL for 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> Three notes:<br>
1) When you get KoS, they will assist each other and the technique with oozes no longer work<br>
2) If you tire of killed normal ones (and dont want faction hits as well) use disintegrate, it works on all lightblues at 60 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
3) Theres a way of getting rid of those ya dont wanna kill the normal ways....it might be exploitage, but then again so much is...aggro a geo, kite it to a section of the caves where theres a small section you can run around (kinda like a column), so that the geonid after ya runs right into the side (where you actually cant see it at that time) Now 80% of the time the geonid will poof, gone as if killed, tho no xps/faction heh. It doesnt matter where ya find this stretch of cave where you can run around, as long as the geonid hits the side smack on and keeps walking into it until poof. Keep it targetted and if it disappears by itself its gone. Enjoy! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
